# Keep LF in the working tree on every platform.
#
# Without this, a Windows checkout rewrites text files to CRLF, and two gates
# fail there for reasons that have nothing to do with the code:
#
#   * templates_test compares a template's .gitignore byte-for-byte against
#     "/shipyard\n" — CRLF makes that "\r\n" and the comparison fails;
#   * pkg/coreaot's drift test regenerates its Go sources (LF, from gofmt)
#     and diffs them against the CRLF copies on disk, so EVERY generated file
#     reports as stale.
#
# cljgo emits Go source and compares generated bytes as a matter of course, so
# LF everywhere is the only setting under which the gates mean the same thing
# on all three platforms.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Binary assets must never be line-ending converted.
*.png binary
*.jpg binary
*.gif binary
*.ico binary
*.pdf binary
